caption: This place is amazing!!! It’s usually busy and for good reason. I highly recommend!
High quality food, interesting decor, wonderful service

There’s a reason it is hard to get a table at Domaine South—it serves up some of the best food and wine in Huntsville right now! We tried the baguette, deviled eggs, and a charcuterie board with fig jam. We also had one of the best pinot noirs I have tried in a while (Lola).

Had an absolutely amazing time here. What a treasure. We did not have a reservation, but we went early in the day and it was not a issue. Told the server what we wanted to spend and to build us a cheese and charcuterie. It was perfect!! We then ordered more! The wine and champagne accompanied it perfectly.
WOW loved my late lunch here. Made happy hour for wine, they answered all my questions and helped guide me to a wine I would like and they did it successfully! Their sandwiches are not to be missed!
Awesome staff, excellent food and wine selection, very cool location
Excellent selection. Great service. Call ahead or you won't get a seat
I had such a positive experience celebrating a special occasion for a friend and colleague thanks to the team at Domaine South, particularly Hazel! Amazing customer service, i so appreciate you all!

Simply the best restaurant in Huntsville for food and atmosphere, wine events, and wine purchases (and amazing recommendations!). Sitting at their bar is my favorite thing in Huntsville. Can’t wait to go again post-covid! I’m the meantime, I will continue to use and appreciate their curbside service.
Great food, wine, atmosphere and service!

Great concept executed excellently. Such a knowledgeable staff that will help with the selection of cheeses, meats, and other accoutrement to make for a perfect afternoon. Somehow we ended up with way too much rind on our board and in a heartbeat they replaced it with a perfect slice.
Amazing food excellent service.This place is a gwm
Absolutely the best brunch in Huntsville. Amazing wine selection. The croque madame is superb! My husband got the smoked salmon and said it was amazing.

Easily the best food in town. A++  Their progressive rotating menu features seasonal meats, fruits and vegetables cooked to perfection. The wine and beer selection is fantastic and the service is always on point. Dogs are allowed on the patio, and the servers are very friendly. If I could give this place a six star rating, I would!  My only critique (wish?) is for more vegetarian and vegan entrées. That being said, there is always something delicious for everyone to enjoy and they are always down to accommodate any food allergies or restrictions.

If you haven’t been to Domaine South yet, you are missing out! I went over the weekend with family for brunch and was not disappointed. Johnathan answered all of our questions about the different dishes and all of our choices were equally delicious - you really can’t make a bad choice here. Will definitely be back for wine another day!
Loved the atmosphere. Best BLT I have ever had. The charcuterie board was great also.
Nice wine ,meat and cheese eatery. Small but cozy. Staff was very friendly. Had good knowledge of there products.

Lunch at Domaine South turned out to be more of an overall great experience than just simply a meal. The venue is so nice and comfortable with an eclectic interior and music piped in at just the right level - loud enough to hear but soft enough to talk over. Our server and menu guide was Heidi and she was marvelous. There was some nice, economical selections of "happy hour" wines and "mystery beers." Our sandwiches were so darn good that you wanted to take more home for later. I had the BLT-DS and my friend had the tuna melt. We shared a creme brulee for dessert. An amazing experience at a very special place. P.S. Room is limited so reservations, even for lunch, are probably a good idea.
This is a little taste of Europe on the corner downtown square in Huntsville.
Wonderfully cozy atmosphere, great staff, amazing flavors. Couldn't be happier with our experience and will definitely be back!
Amazing! Such an incredible spot with outstanding food and service!

Delicious brunch menu! This was my first time here and this little restaurant is so cute. The decor inside is cute. HUGE wine selection. You can buy wine by the bottle here as well to take home. Must make reservations to eat, but I recommend it. It was delicious! I'd love to try dinner here sometime!

First time visit with a couple of friends. The manager visited our table "nice touch" and the staff was somewhat friendly. The food and wine were great. Recommend this place however you should make a reservation and confirm your end time. We made a reservation but were not informed of an end time. We were quite embarrassed when we were  told by a staff member our time was up!!!  We enjoyed the restaurant but disappointed that commuciation was not good. We can respect a timed visit if known up front.
Amazing experience 💕❤️
Great charcuterie. Even better wine!
absolutely love this place! great wine selection, cozy environment, interesting and fresh menu options using local ingredients - a hidden treasure of Huntsville
Great place delicious food and a nice place to meet a friend for lunch!
Came for a quick bite for lunch - tasty and unique flavors in a cozy atmosphere. Will definitely return.
Great wine and good food!

Stopped in to grab some wine and cheese for a date night at home. Staff was very nice, and offered good recommendations for pairings (not my strong suit) and even made sure to double check prices on the cheeses when they seemed too high. Cozy little spot, and we're planning on doing an out of the house date there soon!
Excellent food, wine, beer, and atmosphere
Lobster roll is awesome

The deviled eggs are seriously good. Such a great appetizer! Good wine list for Happy Hour. Non-pretentious, but knowledgeable wait staff. I'd recommend a reservation. It's a tiny place, & they fill up fast.
Great location, great service, great food, reasonable pricing. Put this place on your must visit list.
Always such a pleasure to come here. Great food, superb service, comfortable atmosphere and wonderful friends. What more could you ask for?
Great wine; skimpy but tasty appetizers. $9 for a small slice of ham and some nuts. Deviled eggs are really good. Great atmosphere.

Everything about this spot is outstanding. Ambience, service, charcuterie boards, entrees, and WINE. Plan ahead and make a reservation when you want to visit because it is always full in the smallish dining room. Sidewalk tables were full too when I went on a hot September evening. Yes it is pricey but in my opinion worth the cost. Try it, you'll love it!
All of the dishes I've had are amazing! The deviled eggs were delicious! A must try restaurant!
Reminds me of my home town on the French Riviera so great experience. Possibly needs improvements I would lower the number of employees and raise the portion sizes. Still a good experience.

I joined a group of co-workers for a relaxed evening and Domaine South definitely fit the bill. We dined out on the sidewalk, a nice change from the normal crowded eatery concept. Appetizers chosen ranged from charcuterie boards with meats and cheeses chosen by us, to some of the best deviled eggs I have had recently. The dinner choices were equally varied, from unique twists on classic sandwiches to a limited selection of main dishes. I chose the lamb meatballs, cooked in a slightly spicy sauce and served over a bed of couscous. The meatballs were very tasty, lightly spiced and full of a mild lamb flavor. While I am not normally a fan of couscous, the sauce from the meatballs settled into it and I found myself devouring every trace. I reserve one star back for a couple of minor issues. Firstly, eating alfresco here means sitting on metal folding chairs. One of our party suffered a loss of dignity when the chair decided to give way while he was sitting. Better chairs would alleviate this issue. Secondly, their beer selection lists a dozen or so on tap. However, all are lighter colored brews, from pilsners to the ever trendy IPAs. Not a decent dark beer in sight. The iced tea wasn't bad, though.
Friendly staff, cozy atmosphere in or out. The BLT sandwich is Amazing!!
Went for dessert and port. Excellent espresso creme brulee. Great atmosphere and staff.
The food and the service was fantastic!!!!

I advice to get there early or make a reservation. We got there right when they opened and it was getting packed right when we left. Great options but the bread was a bit too hard for me, other than that, everything was delicious!
Loved this place. Great food and relaxed atmosphere.
I like their wine collection. The place is small but super cute. I wish they have more vegetarian/vegan options.

I shared an amazing charcuterie board (that we were able to build from the menu offerings) with my friend for lunch. Smoked duck & rainbow trout dill spread...amazing!! The wine selections were equally impressive. Our waitress was courteous & helpful making our visit there so comfortable that we stayed longer than we expected to. A definite gem!
Always delicious!

This is quickly becoming our very favorite restaurant in town. The food is fabulous, but I love the inclusive, easy atmosphere. I feel like I'm in a cafe in France while on the West Side of the Square in downtown Huntsville. As a Huntsville native, I am so excited to see a restaurant like this thriving in our city. The food, wine, and atmosphere are on point.
Great wine selection and delicious charcuterie options.

I hope this establishment is here to stay!! We had a wonderful experience from start to finish..our server Amber was able to answer any questions we had and was very intuitive..she suggested wines for us based on our taste preferences and even let us sample them first. The portions on the boards are generous and we were able to fill up on that alone. We had a goat cheese cheescake with a strawberry compote that blew our mind! We can't wait to try some lunch sandwiches.

There is nothing better than a Madeira Wine with coffee crème brûlée.. at Domain South... dessert wine pulls at my heart strings. The flavor is rich , the essence old , wise and slow.. southern slow... cigar smoking slow... methodical .... as in the heat slows your speech to a slur. Steep of my love for the  roots where the magnolia tree blooms with its lemon scents in the late afternoon. The Madeira Wine is a beautiful toasted brown in its glass, the hairdresser in me tries to figure out how to accomplish this color on my next muse. Give yourself a blessing and head to Domain South....
Cozy atmosphere, awesome food, great service and great bar selection.

Local, independently owned. Awesome wine selection. Perfect hideaway for anyone longing for a European style wine bar with charcuterie. Ingredients are locally sourced when available and wine selection is deliberate and thoughtful. Excellent every time.
Great selection of wine and great food.
Great service(Heidi) with a smile. She explained menu items and answered we had, it was our first time there. Food was wonderful and very fresh. Great selection of French wines. We'll be back!!😊
The food is great and unique, and the staff is very attentive.
Great quaint wine bar.

My wife and I have visited Domaine a handful of times now, and have enjoyed each one thoroughly. Excellent wines, and interesting selections on the menu (we always order a charcuterie board). We've had four different servers, each of whom was friendly and very capable of suggesting good wine pairings. During peak hours things get busy, so reservations are a good idea. Particularly given that this is a European-style place where taking your time is valued, the reservation system is more art than science--so if you're OCD about that sort of thing, be prepared. Overall highly recommended.

It's a tiny restaurant packed with surprises. Despite the interiors restroom is must visit. I admire the thought that went into designing this place. I tried the Ricotta, it has to be one of the best dishes I have ever tried. It might be enough in quantity but sure enough with the quality. Must try

Probably one of the most delightful cuisine experience I've ever had. It's  a small place but the food is outstanding. We were there at lunch and they happy hour, with $5 glass select wines/beer. I had a syrah blend. The food- exquisite. I had BLT:DS, with a salad, no words at how good that was. ♥️♥️ My DH had roast beef and that was just as phenomenal.♥️♥️ We tried dessert- the best tiramisu I've ever had-- creamy with a citrus whipped cream. If I wasn't in public or have licked the plate. ♥️♥️ Highly recommend! Go if you can. A wonderful, charming, casual place with the best food! We will go back.

Great quaint wine bar with beer and small bites to eat while enjoying your tasty wine. Including an outdoor seating area to soak up the weather when appropriate. Location is at the corner not far from the park in the center of the downtown area. They even had a few Vegan options! Yaaay!
Great food, great wine, great staff, great environment. This is one of the the best spots in Huntsville.
Great service and unique menu
Tuna melt sandwich was delicious
Wine + food
Great service, great food!
Lovely lunch. Great atmosphere and service.  I plan to go again soon
Great meal! Arugula salad & goat cheese cake were scrumptious

Had an early lunch here with my wife.  Food was excellent, and it's a charming little place with quality wines available for sale.  Had soup, salad and a sandwich and all were excellent.  I look forward to coming back after hours for wine and charcuterie.
This place is crushing it... ABSOLUTELY FABULOUS!!
A FANTASTIC wine experience! They have a fantastic wine selection and the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. The shop itself is lovely and has great gift ideas!
Awesome atmosphere and knowledgeable staff. Good retail selection, as well.

Corner window table accomdates 8 if you snuggle in and the staff does a great job of managing a fine small space.  Soup and bites! Dinner was fantastic and the vibe is great and gracious.  Busy! So plan ahead and expect to share the good space. Great place to make or meet a friend. I ordered a case and recommend the outside space.

AWFUL and I never write reviews. Never going back and was so excited because this looked like an awesome place. The "owner" was incredibly rude to me today. I came in for lunch with a girlfriend of mine and was sitting comfortably at a table. My friend had to leave early and I was still enjoying my glass of wine alone. I would have no problem being asked to move to a smaller table for a larger party, but She rudely came over and told me that she had the table "reserved" at 12:30 and placed a sign on the table that I was sitting at. I mentioned to her that it was 12:34 because I thought it was so odd, and she told me to move. I love downtown Huntsville and I'm always in for a new place. I live within walking distance of this one. I also own a local business. I support local and I thought Domaine South would be my new go to lunch spot. Never again. Thanks for making me feel uncomfortable, not welcome, and being super unfriendly.
Great service and food.  We eat a plant based diet and they were very helpful and accommodating. I  highly recommend Domaine South...we will be making this a regular outing.
Loved it! Great experience but would definitely recommend reservations! Will definitely be back and the staff was wonderful!
My new favorite restaurant in Huntsville. The cheese and charcuterie menu was almost completely different the second time we went. And it's all Great!
Can't say enough about this place. It's warm and inviting, super knowledgeable staff, delicious food and wine. 10/10
Love love love!
Very good Beef Bourguignon!
True gourmet eclectic international bistro style
Fantastic wine shop with delicious food. Kristian is incredibly knowledgeable, and sure to find you something you'll like. It is a small space, so reservations are a good idea.
Staff was helpful to help pick out wine. Seems like an upscale place.
Great addition to the downtown food scene. Go on Saturdays for a free wine tasting and grab a cheese board while you're at it!
Great atmosphere with fabulous food and wine.
Don South is simply excellent; excellent atmosphere, wine, service and food every time I go. A great ( and needed) addition to the downtown scene ....
Always an amazing place to go to, lunch or dinner. Best place for a girl's night or date night. The location is small, so I make a reservation when I go with a group.
Great food. Awesome beer and wine selection.
Great wine, Great staff, Great food, and Great Experience!!!
This place is amazing, highly recommended. The owners are super nice and the food is delicious. Nice selection of wines as well. Defyingly stop in.
Wonderful shop with incredibly knowledgeable owner.

The best little wine shop in Huntsville, but also so much more!  Domaine South is a place to find unique gifts (often locally-made!!), cookbooks,  yummy cheeses, and wine tastings.  The owner, Kristian, is a lovely person with a lot of knowledge to share - definitely ask her for wine recommendations!!

Hands down, a five star experience. This gourmet wine, cheese and gift shop compares to my favorites in big cities around the country. A small, locally-owned shop, Domaine South has a highly curated selection and an owner who knows how to pair every bottle with your meal, gift or event.

Truly the best place in Huntsville to pick up a bottle of wine or a gift. Everything is delightful and kind of unexpected. Kristian is great about making suggestions and finding delicious wines that fit your budget. Stop in, you won't regret it.
